'''Arindam Ghosh''' is an Associate Professor in the Department of Physics, [[Indian Institute of Science]], [[Bangalore]], [[India]]. He was awarded the [[Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize]] for science and technology, the highest science award in India, for the year 2012 in physical science category.<ref>{{cite web|title=SHANTI SWARUP BHATNAGAR AWARDS 2012 |url=http://www.dst.gov.in/awards/award12.htm |publisher=Department of Science & Technology, Government of India |accessdate=17 January 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140405001144/http://dst.gov.in/awards/award12.htm |archivedate=5 April 2014 }}</ref> He did his PhD at the [[Indian Institute of Science]]. His current research interests include the transport properties of two-dimensional electronic systems in [[semiconductor]]s, carbon-based low-dimensional systems, optoelectronic properties of atomically-thin semiconductor membranes, magnetic [[nanostructure]]s, and structural stability of nanoscale systems such as metallic [[nanowire]]s and [[nanoparticle]]s.<ref>{{cite web|title=Arindam Ghosh |url=http://www.physics.iisc.ernet.in/~arindam/people/CV_Arindam%20Ghosh%20July%202013.pdf |publisher=Indian Institute of Science |accessdate=17 January 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131001030640/http://www.physics.iisc.ernet.in/~arindam/people/CV_Arindam%20Ghosh%20July%202013.pdf |archivedate=1 October 2013 }}</ref> 

