'''Balchen Glacier''' ({{Coord|76|23|S|145|10|W|source:GNIS}}) is a crevassed [[glacier]] in [[Antarctica]], flowing west to [[Block Bay]] between the [[Phillips Mountains]] and the [[Fosdick Mountains]] in [[Marie Byrd Land]]. It was discovered on December 5, 1929, by the [[Byrd Antarctic Expedition]] and named by [[Richard E. Byrd]] for [[Bernt Balchen]], chief pilot of the expedition.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://geographic.org/geographic_names/antname.php?uni=884&fid=antgeo_102 | title = Balchen Glacier | website = Geographical names | accessdate = 16 January 2018}}</ref>
