'''Lucas Friedrich Julius Dominikus von Heyden''' (22 May 1838, [[Frankfurt]] – 13 September 1915, Frankfurt) was a [[Germany|German]] [[entomologist]] specialising in [[Coleoptera]] beetles.  He wrote with [[Edmund Reitter]] and [[Ján Weiss]] ''Catalogus coleopterorum Europae, Caucasi et Armeniae rossicae''. Edn 2. Berlin, Paskau, Caen(1902).

