'''Nanostrain''' is an EU-funded project to characterise [[piezoelectric]] materials for future fast digital switch designs.<ref>[http://www.electronicsweekly.com/university-electronics/general/nanostrain-project-plans-to-characterise-piezoelectric-materials-2013-11/#sthash.gfuXjSEd.dpuf Nanostrain project plans to characterise piezoelectric materials. Nov 2013]</ref><ref>[http://www.npl.co.uk/news/new-global-research-effort-to-measure-nanoscale-strain New global research effort to measure nanoscale strain. Nov 2013]</ref>
The switching may only need a much lower voltage and be faster with lower power consumption than [[CMOS]].<ref>[http://www2.warwick.ac.uk/fac/cross_fac/xmas/nanostrainproject/ EMRP Nanostrain Project - XMaS]</ref>
